&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Maddox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maddox is the nation’s leading provider of electrical transformers to the commercial and industrial market, with primary locations in South Carolina, Washington State, Texas, Idaho, and Ohio. We have been recognized by &lt;em&gt;Inc. Magazine&lt;/em&gt; as one of the fastest-growing companies in America for the past 8 years and counting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maddox was founded on Christian values, and we are serious about investing in the people, processes, and culture that make this a great place to work. We build real things, solve real problems, and expect professionalism, competence, and integrity from our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Discover more at:&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/@MaddoxTransformer&quot;&gt;https://www.youtube.com/@MaddoxTransformer&lt;br&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.maddox.com/&quot;&gt;https://www.maddox.com/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Maddox + You:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a &lt;strong&gt;highly capable, experienced Executive Administrator&lt;/strong&gt; to provide direct, high-trust support to the CEO of a growing, multi-company organization spanning manufacturing, real estate, hospitality, and community initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is for an experienced EA who thrives close to executive decision-making and takes pride in &lt;strong&gt;protecting time, managing priorities, and ensuring disciplined execution.&lt;/strong&gt; As EA, you will assist in day-to-day activities —reducing friction, increasing clarity, and lightening cognitive load to enable the CEO to remain focused on the highest-value work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a mid-sized, high-growth company, this position offers &lt;strong&gt;meaningful long-term career growth&lt;/strong&gt; for the right person.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Executive &amp;amp; Calendar Management&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and manage a complex executive calendar across multiple companies and initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate internal and external meetings, ensuring clear agendas, preparation, and follow-up&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify conflicts, capacity constraints, and priority trade-offs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare daily and weekly briefing materials, agendas, and reminders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication &amp;amp; Gatekeeping&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a trusted point of contact for senior leaders, partners, advisors, and select external stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft, review, and organize executive correspondence as directed – managing emails, calls, liaison for visitors and screening what goes to other leaders and what needs the CEO’s attention (and when).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Screen and prioritize inbound communications with sound judgment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track commitments, action items, and follow-through – meeting minutes, prep and follow up documents, key decisions/next steps, meeting agendas, and other key research and reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel, Meetings &amp;amp; Logistics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate travel, itineraries, and meeting logistics in coordination with our Corporate Travel team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support planning and execution of leadership meetings, offsites, and key events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational &amp;amp; Project Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with light project coordination and execution across multiple operating companies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize and maintain files, records, and reference materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support special initiatives, research, and ad-hoc reques

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Maddox&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maddox is the nation’s leading provider of electrical transformers to the commercial and industrial market, with primary locations in South Carolina, Washington State, Texas, Idaho, and Ohio. We have been recognized by &lt;em&gt;Inc. Magazine&lt;/em&gt; as one of the fastest-growing companies in America for the past 8 years and counting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maddox was founded on Christian values, and we are serious about investing in the people, processes, and culture that make this a great place to work. We build real things, solve real problems, and expect professionalism, competence, and integrity from our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Discover more at:&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/@MaddoxTransformer&quot;&gt;https://www.youtube.com/@MaddoxTransformer&lt;br&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.maddox.com/&quot;&gt;https://www.maddox.com/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Maddox PRO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Maddox PRO is a shared services organization and sister company to Maddox Industrial Transformer, the nation’s leading provider of electrical transformers to the commercial and industrial market. PRO stands for Professional Resource Organization. We exist so Maddox can stay focused on building and selling transformers while we handle the surrounding work: facilities acquisition, development, construction, and maintenance across all Maddox locations, along with community engagement and business investments in the towns where Maddox operates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maddox PRO was founded on the same Christian values that drive Maddox, and we are committed to investing in the people, processes, and culture that make this a great place to work. We build real things, solve real problems, and believe that a thriving business and a thriving community go hand in hand.&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Maddox PRO + You:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We are seeking a dependable and detail-oriented Facilities Support team member to help maintain clean, welcoming, and well-kept spaces across our Battle Ground campus. This role is essential to keeping our workspaces and client-facing areas clean, safe, and functional. You&#39;ll be part of a team that takes pride in creating a hospitable environment for our employees and guests.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;More about You:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Your key responsibilities will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform daily janitorial duties at multiple Maddox buildings (offices, retail, and Airbnb spaces)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Indoor and outdoor cleaning, including sweeping, mopping, vacuuming, and trash removal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean and restock restrooms, and respond to cleaning needs throughout the day&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with setup and teardown for company events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support seasonal deep-cleaning projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and report any maintenance issues or safety hazards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience &amp;amp; Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently and take initiative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Valid driver’s license required for travel between sites&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and teamwork skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to work before or after normal business hours to avoid disrupting operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Schedule:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Two shifts available: 5:00 AM – 2:00 PM or 10:00 AM – 7:00 PM&lt;br&gt;This role may be filled by either two part-time positions or one full-time employee.&lt;/p&gt;
